descriptions.description:
Abiotic and biotic data from all sampling dates. 
plotid = Plot ID;
date = Sample date;
rep = Replicate;
trt = Water level treatment (0 cm, -10 cm, -20 cm, -30 cm);
cover = Cover treatment (HP = Herbaceous plants, LS = Low shrub, WM = Wood-strand mulch, NC = No-cover control, C = No-moss no-cover control);
gwc = Gravimetric water content;
l = Percent cover of litter;
tdiff = Temperature difference between surface and 5 cm depth in the soil (C o);
s2aw = distance between the soil and average water level (cm);
som = Percent soil organic matter;
tmb = Moss biomass 	(g);
om = Percent cover of opportunistic mosses;	
tm = Percent cover of total moss;
om14 = Percent cover of opportunistic mosses in September 2014;
tm14 = Percent cover of total moss in September 2014;
ll01 = Percent cover litter transformed using a logit;
tdiffsq = Temp difference between surface and 5 cm depth in the soil transformed with a square root;
tmbsq = Soil organic matter transformed with a square root;
oml01 = Percent cover of opportunistic mosses transformed using a logit;
tmsq = Percent cover of total moss transformed with a square root;
om14l01 = Percent cover of opportunistic mosses in Sept 2014 transformed using a logit;
tm14l01 = Percent cover of total moss in Sept 2014 transformed with a square root;
